## Day 1:

Today is pull day, but I still have a bit of a fever and GERD messing with me, so I vomited during my 3rd set of pull-ups. Nevertheless, I carried on, trying to reduce the symptoms by drinking water to neutralise the stomach acid somewhat, and it worked

Anyway, since this is my first day of the gym after more than 2 months (2 months and 13 days to be precise) and I have my half-sister's wedding to attend to tomorrow, I was only able to work out for 30 minutes, of which today's session is:

- Pull ups (10 reps, 5 reps, 5 reps, 4 reps, 3 reps)
- Cable rows 8 stacks so that's probably around 50 kg (10 reps, 5 reps, 5 reps, 5 reps, 4 reps)
- Supinated dumbbell curls 10 kg (10 reps, 5 reps, 5 reps, 5 reps, 5 reps)

Content:
Alright so, I shouldn't have worked out that intensely today. I've been feeling sick the whole day, and I didn't listen to my body

So, this is a lesson, there's this rule of thumb called the "neck rule". If you're feeling unwill above the neck (snotty, coughing, etc), then you can probably do light workout

But if you're feeling unwell below the neck (aches, sensitive skin, fever, and so on), then rest
